article.headline: Monmouth, N.J. 17, Duquesne 10
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. -- David Sinisi ran for 122 yards and a touchdown and Monmouth forced four second-half turnovers to beat Duquesne 17-10 on Saturday. The Hawks (1-2, 1-0 Northeast Conference) trailed 10-7 after Duquesne's Kevin Rombach connected with Marek Lapinski on an 11-yard pass with 32 seconds left in the first half. Rombach finished with 252 yards passing and two interceptions for the Dukes (1-2, 0-1). But Monmouth tied the game at 10-10 in the third quarter on Eric McCutchen's 30-yard field. Duquesne took over at its own 4-yard line and drove past midfield before Monmouth's Kendall Haley intercepted a Rombach pass, returning it 65 yards for a touchdown as the Hawks sealed the game. Sinisi, who finished with 32 carries, scored on a 1-yard run in the first quarter. Cleodis Williams led the Dukes with 109 rushing yards on 23 carries.
